    <introduction>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p>Residents of an Edinburgh hospice facility are the first palliative care patients in Scotland to experience the stunning effects of virtual reality in an exciting new university research project. The interactive initiative, which can virtually transport patients to locations on the other side of the world, will look at the impact of virtual reality (VR) on patients’ health and wellbeing.</p>]]></Value>
