    <notesToEditors>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://viarama.co.uk/" title="Viarama website"><strong>About Viarama</strong></a></p>
<p><strong>Viarama is Scotland’s first virtual reality company, and the world’s first virtual reality Social Enterprise. </strong>It uses the innovative power of VR as a force for good within communities across Scotland, working to specifically improve the quality of life of schoolchildren, senior citizens, and 18-24 year olds. Viarama works in many sectors including education and healthcare, and is committed to training and employing 18-24-year-olds to deliver VR to schools, nursing homes, hospices, and respite centres. It also works on a variety of exciting and innovative VR projects in partnership with government and industry, and all of its work has a strong focus on improving quality of life. Viarama allows people of all ages and all levels of physical ability to enjoy the best virtual reality experiences available in the world today.  </p>
<p>Viarama provided VR experiences to the residents of St Columba's Hospice free of charge for the duration of the initial pilot; approximately one year.</p>
<p><strong>Virtual Reality Headsets</strong></p>
<p>Viarama uses the HTC Vive VR Headset which was recently voted as device of the year by several noted magazines and tech websites. To power the headsets, it uses the most powerful pc’s available; custom built from the ground up to provide an experience second to none anywhere in the world.</p>
<p><strong>St Columba’s Hospice</strong></p>
<p>Find <a href="https://stcolumbashospice.org.uk/" title="St Columba's Hospice website">more information about St Columba's Hospice</a> on their website. </p>
<p><strong>About Queen Margaret University, Edinburgh</strong></p>
<p>QMU is renowned for relevant research and knowledge exchange work which focuses on making a positive impact on society. The University has widely recognised expertise in health &amp; rehabilitation, sustainable business, and creativity &amp; culture.</p>
<p>Staff in <a href="/schools-and-divisions/nursing/" title="QMU Nursing Division">QMU’s Division of Nursing</a> are passionate about excellent person-centred and evidence-informed practice and are engaged in a range of impactful research projects.</p>
<p>For further media information please contact Lynne Russell, Communications Manager, Queen Margaret University, Edinburgh, E: <a href="mailto:lrussell@qmu.ac.uk">lrussell@qmu.ac.uk</a>, <em>T: </em>0131 474 0000, M: 07711 011239 or Chelsie Harris, PR Manager at St Columba Hospice, E: media@stcolumbashospice.org.uk<em>. T: </em>0131 551 1381</p>]]></Value>
